---
// Cryptogram — Privacy Policy
// NOTE: This document is informational only and does not constitute legal
// advice. The owner should review (ideally with a qualified professional)
// before publishing.
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import LegalPage from "../../components/LegalPage.astro";

const effectiveDate = "27 June 2026";
---

<Layout title="Cryptogram Privacy Policy">
  <LegalPage title="Cryptogram Privacy Policy" lastUpdated={effectiveDate}>
    <section>
      <p>
        <strong>Effective date: {effectiveDate}</strong>
      </p>
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how Shareef Solutions ("Company," "we,"
        "us," or "our") handles information in connection with
        <strong>Cryptogram</strong>, a free Android puzzle game (package id
        <strong>com.shareef.cryptogram</strong>) (the "App" or the "Game"). It
        applies only to the Cryptogram App and not to any other product or
        website. By downloading or using the App, you agree to the practices
        described in this Policy.
      </p>
      <p>
        See also our <a href="/cryptogram/terms">Cryptogram Terms &amp;
        Conditions</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>1. What We Collect and What We Do Not Collect</h2>
      <p>
        Cryptogram is designed to work without accounts and without collecting
        personal information from you directly.
      </p>
      <h3>We do not collect</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          No accounts, login, or registration. The App does not require you to
          create an account or sign in.
        </li>
        <li>
          No personal contact information. We do not collect your name, email
          address, phone number, or similar contact details.
        </li>
        <li>
          No device location permission. The App does not request access to your
          device location (GPS) and does not collect precise location.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Stored locally on your device</h3>
      <p>
        All gameplay data — including puzzle progress, coins, streaks, and
        settings — is stored locally on your device in a local SQLite database.
        This data stays on your device. There is no Shareef Solutions backend
        server, this information is not transmitted to us, and we do not have
        access to it.
      </p>
      <h3>Collected by our advertising provider</h3>
      <p>
        The App shows ads, and our advertising provider (Google AdMob) and its
        partners may collect certain device and usage information through the
        App. This is described in the next section.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2. Advertising and Third-Party Data (Google AdMob)</h2>
      <p>
        The App displays advertisements through Google AdMob, including banner,
        interstitial, and rewarded ad formats. To serve and measure ads, Google
        AdMob and its partners may collect and process information such as:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Device identifiers</li>
        <li>Advertising ID (Google Advertising ID)</li>
        <li>IP address</li>
        <li>Coarse (approximate) location inferred from your IP address</li>
        <li>App-usage and ad-interaction data</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Depending on your region and your consent choices, ads may be
        personalized and/or non-personalized. This processing is carried out by
        Google and its advertising partners under their own policies. The App
        itself does not request device location permission; any location used
        for advertising is approximate and inferred by Google from your IP
        address.
      </p>
      <p>
        For details on how Google uses information from apps that use its
        services, see <a
          href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites</a
        >.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>3. Consent and Your Choices</h2>
      <h3>Consent for personalized ads (EEA / UK)</h3>
      <p>
        For users in the European Economic Area, the United Kingdom, and other
        regions where it is required, the App uses Google's User Messaging
        Platform (UMP) consent flow to request consent for personalized ads as
        required by the GDPR. You can change or withdraw your consent at any time
        from the App's Settings.
      </p>
      <h3>Opting out of ad personalization</h3>
      <p>
        You can choose to receive non-personalized ads instead of personalized
        ads through the consent options described above and through your device
        settings.
      </p>
      <h3>Resetting or deleting your advertising ID</h3>
      <p>
        You can reset or delete your advertising ID and opt out of ad
        personalization at the device level in
        <strong>Android Settings → Google → Ads</strong>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>4. Your Rights Under the GDPR (EEA / UK)</h2>
      <p>
        If you are located in the EEA or the UK, you have rights under the GDPR,
        including the right to access, rectify, erase, restrict, or object to the
        processing of your personal data, the right to data portability, and the
        right to withdraw consent at any time. You also have the right to lodge a
        complaint with your local data protection supervisory authority.
      </p>
      <p>
        Because the App has no accounts and no backend, we do not ourselves hold
        personal data that identifies you. Advertising-related data is processed
        by Google and its partners as described above. To exercise rights over
        that data, you can use the in-app consent controls and the device
        controls described in Section 3, and refer to Google's policies. For any
        questions about our handling of your information, contact us at the
        address in Section 9.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>5. Your California Privacy Rights (CCPA / CPRA)</h2>
      <h3>Do Not Sell or Share My Personal Information</h3>
      <p>
        We do not sell your personal information for money. However, the sharing
        of device and usage data with advertising partners for personalized or
        cross-context behavioral advertising may be considered a "sale" or
        "sharing" under the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), as amended by
        the CPRA.
      </p>
      <p>You can opt out of this personalized advertising by:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Declining or withdrawing consent for personalized ads via the in-app
          consent options (see Section 3);
        </li>
        <li>
          Resetting your advertising ID and turning off ad personalization in
          <strong>Android Settings → Google → Ads</strong>; and
        </li>
        <li>Using Google AdMob's advertising opt-out controls.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        California residents also have the right to know about, access, delete,
        and correct personal information, and the right not to receive
        discriminatory treatment for exercising these rights. To make a request,
        contact us using the details in Section 9.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>6. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Cryptogram is a general-audience game and is not directed to children
        under 13 (or under the minimum age of digital consent in your
        jurisdiction). We do not knowingly collect personal information from
        children. If you believe a child has provided personal information
        through the App, please contact us and we will take appropriate steps.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>7. Data Retention and Deletion</h2>
      <p>
        Because gameplay data is stored only locally on your device, it remains
        there until you remove it. You can delete this data at any time by
        clearing the App's data or by uninstalling the App. We do not hold any
        server-side personal data about you, so there is nothing for us to delete
        on our side. For advertising data held by Google and its partners, please
        use the controls described in Section 3 and Google's policies.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>8. Security</h2>
      <p>
        Your local gameplay data is stored on your device and protected by your
        device's operating system and security settings. Advertising and in-app
        purchases are handled by Google over encrypted connections. While we and
        our service providers take reasonable measures to protect information, no
        method of electronic storage or transmission is 100% secure, and we
        cannot guarantee absolute security.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will
        revise the "Effective date" at the top of this page. Your continued use
        of the App after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the updated
        Policy.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or
        your information, please contact us:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Email: <a href="mailto:nadeemshareef934@gmail.com"
            >nadeemshareef934@gmail.com</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>Location: Hyderabad, India</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </LegalPage>
</Layout>
